  "body": "building function return disposal function is a common usage in a lot of API, for example in `rxjs`:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nRx.Observable.create(observer => {\r\n    let timeoutId = setTimeout(...);\r\n    return () => {              \r\n        clearTimeout(timeoutId);\r\n    };\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nso suggest `componentDidMount` return `componentWillUnmount`\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nexport class XX extends React.Component {\r\n    componentDidMount() {\r\n       let timeoutId = setTimeout(...);\r\n             \r\n       return function componentWillUnmount() {\r\n           clearTimeout(timeoutId);\r\n       }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\notherwise, the `timeoutId` will must be augment scope to instance member `this.timeoutId`. the code is:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nexport class XX extends React.Component {\r\n    componentDidMount() {\r\n       this.timeoutId = setTimeout(...);\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    componentWillUnmount() {\r\n       clearTimeout(this.timeoutId);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
